header.gameNote: ONEIDA BINGO & CASINO CLASSIC AT GREEN BAY WI

article.headline: Bowling Green 58, Michigan Tech 46
article.story: GREEN BAY, Wis. (AP) -- Ryne Hamblet came off the bench to lead Bowling Green with 18 points and 11 rebounds, as the Falcons beat Michigan Tech 58-46 Wednesday night at the Oneida Casino Holiday Classic. Martin Samarco added 16 points and Nate Miller finished with nine points and nine rebounds for Bowling Green (8-3). The Huskies (6-5) were led by Tim Strom with 13 points, but Michigan Tech leading scorer Radayl Richardson, who came in averaging 17.1 points per game, was limited to just four on 2-of-9 shooting. Bowling Green held Michigan Tech to just 5-of-24 shooting from the field in building a 29-15 halftime lead. The Huskies went on a 9-0 run early in the second half to get within eight points at 34-26 with 13:34 left. But Hamblet hit back-to-back 3-pointers to spark the Bowling Green on a 12-0 spurt.
